  "body": "In the testing docs I see CJS is still the way to pull in the TestUtils directly. When I tried to use ES6 instead like below I get the error `Cannot resolve module 'react-addons-test-utils`\n\n``` js\nimport TestUtils from 'react-addons-test-utils';\n```\n\nWhen I do the legacy import ES6 (like below) I get `Warning: require('react/addons') is deprecated. Access it using require('react-addons-{addon}') instead.`\n\n``` js\nimport React from 'react/addons';\nconst TestUtils = React.addons.TestUtils;\n```\n",
